HEADWORD: Clinometric
<hw>Clin`o*met"ric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pertaining to, or ascertained by, the clinometer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to the oblique crystalline forms, or to
solids which have oblique angles between the axes; <as>as, the
<ex>clinometric</ex> systems</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clinometry</ent>⟦br⟧
